Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.personal.psu.edu/students/b/t/btk120/MOKONA.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> It's not easy.</span><hr size=1> To steal DAoC slang:   BAF (bring a friend).<br>
<br>
Not sure you can do this alone.  If they sell invis potions at 11 plat a pop, you could always take a gamble with one of those.<br>
<br>
 <p>--Antoin Nolouj &lt;League of Shadows&gt;
<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/utitaisia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Titaisia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/9/02 10:39:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1068.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Traveling question from Shar Vahl to the Nexus</span><hr size=1> Actually, if you are careful, you can sneak the whole way.  Just stay far away from all the meanies, and circle behind them.  I did that for a long time.  Scary, but it works.  ^_^  I would only advise it if you already know the way through, though, or if you are following someone who does.<br>
<br>
You could try and see if anyone will cast invisibillity on you, then run through.<br>
<br>
You could group with a jharin that knows Shauri's and have her walk you through - just stay close!  Hope this helped a little. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kiya>Kiya</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalWhite.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Incense-burnin' Fishergirl</span><br>  Posts: 88<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/9/02 10:44:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1068.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Traveling question from Shar Vahl to the Nexus</span><hr size=1> I made it from Shadowhaven to Shar Vahl via Paludal Caverns invisible, and it was pretty scary. My invis (gather shadows) broke once, and I shadowstepped into one of the lakes there, then gated and tried again. If you do try to do this, make sure you have a map handy, and turn your gamma up all the way, cuz it is dark in there, and quite a few elevation changes to confuse you. Good luck, make sure to bank your stuff first. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><i><b><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=42744"><font color="#5D0063">Kiya</font><a/></b></i> - <font size="1">Indigo Void<br>
<a href="http://eq.guildmagic.com/character.cfm?ID=112664">Necro-Fisher of the 12th Circle and 65th Cast</a></font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ustormtower.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Stormtower</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Travelling Circus</span><br>  Posts: 311<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/9/02 11:23:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1068.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Traveling question from Shar Vahl to the Nexus</span><hr size=1> <br>
Aye.  You will definitely need the help of a seasoned traveller who has a map.<br>
<br>
If you can hire the help of a bard with his beguiling song, the two of you are 99% guaranteed a safe passage thru the Paluldal Caverns.<br>
<br>
The other alternative is to find a druid or a wizard with the knowledge of portal magics.<br>
<br>
OOC:<br>
But here's some real advice:  Shadeweaver's Thicket has a lot of great hunting spots for a level 10 to 14 character.  The bandits, poachers, gor taku, etc spawn far faster than any other I've seen (except Warrens).  There are merchants, guards, and a bank in the same zone, so you can save a lot of downtime.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ufoots.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Foots</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/9/02 12:54:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1068.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Traveling question from Shar Vahl to the Nexus</span><hr size=1> I did this at 9th via the Hollowshade Moor route using just sneak.  <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.eqatlas.com/luclin/paludalcavernsmap.html">www.eqatlas.com/luclin/paludalcavernsmap.html</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
I'd scouted it out beforehand with a rogue.  I chose the Hollowshade route ( past the 3 lakes ) because there were no fiends in the tunnels from that zone.  I was very worried about aggroing the fiends guarding the bridge around -1000,500 on the map, but aparantly sneak reduces aggro enough that you can get past them if you swing wide around behind them and then hug the edge of the lakeside cliff.  There are wanderers near the bridge so keep an eye out.<br>
<br>
*** Bank everything before you go and con everything to see where you are vulnerble. ***<br>
<br>
It was very exciting though. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Good Luck,<br>
Pawes <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umadrain.showPublicProfile?language=EN>madrain</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Kerran Lord</span><br>  Posts: 148<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/9/02 1:59:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1068.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Traveling question from Shar Vahl to the Nexus</span><hr size=1> Once I decided just to &quot;go for it&quot; and I ran for it, no invis, no SoW, and I actually nearly made it.  It'd have been a cakewalk with SoW.  I got to the ledge that spirals down, nearly in view of the bandit camps, when I was hit and stunned and then taken low enough that I couldn't run anymore.<br>
<br>
Of course, I'd made the trip several times by sneaking and hiding, but... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/udazzani.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dazzani</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/9/02 6:42:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1068.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Traveling question from Shar Vahl to the Nexus</span><hr size=1> Go via the cave route from the Moor.... you can sneak around the feinds and stay high on the wall. Once you hit the large pool outside of Shadow Haven dive in and swim... pretty easy going that way. This is the way I use to travel, but now at the 30th season I no longer need to sneak around them. The feinds stop aggroing you at the 30th season and that makes travel very much easier...<br>
<br>
If you ever see me online, and I am near by I would be willing to show you the way. Send me a mystical message and I will see what I can do.<br>
<br>
Dazzani Frostpaw &amp; Frostpaw the Warder<br>
30th season Vah' Shir Beastlord <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukisarintenamin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KisarinTenamin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/9/02 8:05:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1068.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Traveling question from Shar Vahl to the Nexus</span><hr size=1> Find a Jharin of 19songs, they can get you through easily with no troubles what so ever.  Just stay close to them and make sure you both have solid connections. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uvallshadowstrife.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vall Shadowstrife</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/10/02 11:20:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1068.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Traveling question from Shar Vahl to the Nexus</span><hr size=1> Bah, I passed through here when I was level 3. Of course, I'm a rogue, so I was pretty safe. Basically, if you've got sneak/hide, you can muck around all you want. I even got up into some Pharlog faces and took some snapshots for the ol' scrapbook. I didn't know you could get to Shadeweaver's from there, and instead took the way from Paludal to Hollowshade to Shar Vahl to Shadeweaver's. Ironically enough, I didn't die in Paludal once, but constantly got killed when I had the gates of Shar Vahl in sight.  <p>Vall Shadowstrife <BR>
Tier'Dal Scout of Luclin <BR>
Agent of The Ring</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/utitaisia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Titaisia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/10/02 11:34:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1068.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Traveling question from Shar Vahl to the Nexus</span><hr size=1> Poor Vall.<br>
<br>
Now that I think about it, I don't think I have ever seen a Tier'Dal visiting Shar Vahl... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uvallshadowstrife.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vall Shadowstrife</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/10/02 1:14:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1068.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Traveling question from Shar Vahl to the Nexus</span><hr size=1> I used to be in Shadeweaver's all the time. I was the guy that the Beastlords tried to have their pets attack. Anyway, I've moved back down to Norrath. <br>
<br>
Update on sneak/hide through Paludal: Watch out for those wall traps. I was sneaking/hiding through Paludal Caverns from Shadeweaver's to Shadow Haven, when I recalled some posts on Allakhazam about spores in the walls/traps. I did sense traps a couple times, and tried to stay away from the walls. Anyway, as I was coming through, I accidentally triggered a trap, and was about three feet away from a Pharlog. Knocked me right out of hide. I hit my hide button as fast as my Captain Crunch-fueled reflexes could, and got back into hide before I could get killed. One've my scariest EQ experiences ever :P <p>Vall Shadowstrife <BR>
Tier'Dal Scout of Luclin <BR>
Agent of The Ring</p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#A62A2A>- </font><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie>Firiona Vie</a><font color=#A62A2A> - </font><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1>Firiona Vie General Chat</a> <font color=#A62A2A> - </font><a href="http://www.firionavie.org/">Firiona Vie</a><font color=#A62A2A> - </font> <center><a href="http://www.firiona-vie.com/fvchat.html" target="_blank"><h3>Chat Room</a></h3></center> <br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 6.6.2<br>Copyright ©1999-2001 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  